Scenario 8 — Cache Reuse After Escalation ("Never Pay Twice")
This tests the full round-trip:

On SWE-1.6, ask: Do a deep dive into the expense tracker architecture
Expected: 🔴 escalation block (Step 0 triggers)
Switch model to Claude Sonnet 4.6 Thinking, resend the same message
Expected: ### 🔴 Expert AI — Escalated (Paid Model) banner, detailed answer, conclusions cached into .virtual-context
Switch back to SWE-1.6, ask: Tell me more about the expense tracker architecture
Expected: ### 🟡 Virtual Context (JIT) — Cache Read — reads the cached Expert AI conclusions, does NOT re-trigger Step 0 (no new deterministic trigger phrase introduced)
Verify:

✅ Step 3 uses cache, not escalation
✅ No paid model call on the follow-up
✅ If you re-introduce a trigger phrase (e.g., Do a comprehensive review of the architecture), it should re-trigger Step 0
